  "text": "## CRD Validation to OpenAPI Schema Publishing Chain\n\nThis document traces the complete flow of how a CustomResourceDefinition's validation schema is converted to an OpenAPI schema in kubernetes/kubernetes and published via the API server.\n\n### 1. CRD Validation Spec (Input)\n\nThe process starts with a CustomResourceDefinition (CRD) object defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apis/apiextensions/v1/types.go`. Each CRD has:\n- A `Spec.Validation` field of type `CustomResourceValidation`\n- Which contains an `OpenAPIV3Schema` field of type `JSONSchemaProps` (OpenAPI schema definition)\n- Additional fields for defining validation rules via `XValidations`\n\n### 2. Structural Schema Extraction\n\nThe key conversion happens in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/convert.go`:\n\n**NewStructural()** function:\n- Takes `JSONSchemaProps` (the CRD's validation schema) as input\n- Converts it to an internal `Structural` schema representation\n- Extracts:\n  - Type information\n  - Properties and additionalProperties\n  - Items (array element schema)\n  - Validation constraints (format, pattern, min/max values, etc.)\n  - Kubernetes-specific extensions (x-kubernetes-list-type, x-kubernetes-preserve-unknown-fields, etc.)\n  - Validation extensions (x-kubernetes-validations for CEL rules)\n- Recursively processes nested properties and items\n\nThe `Structural` type is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/apiserver/schema/structural.go` and serves as an intermediate representation optimized for validation and OpenAPI generation.\n\n### 3. OpenAPI Schema Generation\n\nThe conversion from structural schema to OpenAPI happens in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/builder/builder.go`:\n\n**BuildOpenAPIV3()** and **BuildOpenAPIV2()** functions:\n- Accept a CRD and version name\n- Call `generateBuilder()` which:\n  1. Extracts the OpenAPI schema for the specific version\n  2. Converts it to internal JSONSchemaProps format\n  3. Validates it has no invalid types\n  4. Converts JSONSchemaProps → Structural schema via `NewStructural()`\n  5. Unfolds the structural schema to expand vendor extensions\n  6. Strips value validations or nullable fields if requested\n- Builds a REST WebService with all CRD operations (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE) for:\n  - List operations\n  - Create operations\n  - Individual resource operations with support for subresources (status, scale)\n- Converts the WebService to OpenAPI spec using:\n  - `builder3.BuildOpenAPISpecFromRoutes()` for OpenAPI v3\n  - `openapibuilder.BuildOpenAPISpecFromRoutes()` for OpenAPI v2\n\nThe schema includes Kubernetes native properties (apiVersion, kind, metadata) and handles both namespaced and cluster-scoped resources.\n\n### 4. CRD Controllers that Manage OpenAPI Updates\n\nTwo controllers watch CRD changes and rebuild OpenAPI specs:\n\n**OpenAPI v2 Controller** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/controller.go`):\n- Watches all CRDs via informer\n- For each CRD, builds OpenAPI v2 specs for all served versions\n- Merges all CRD specs together with the static API server spec\n- Updates `handler.OpenAPIService` via `UpdateSpecLazy()`\n- Publishes merged spec at `/openapi/v2`\n\n**OpenAPI v3 Controller** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapiv3/controller.go`):\n- Watches all CRDs via informer\n- For each CRD version, calls `buildV3Spec()` which invokes `BuildOpenAPIV3()`\n- Stores specs organized by GroupVersion\n- Updates `handler3.OpenAPIService.UpdateGroupVersion()` with built specs\n- Publishes specs at `/openapi/v3/<group>/<version>`\n\nBoth controllers respond to CRD additions, updates, and deletions in real-time.\n\n### 5. API Server Endpoint Publication\n\n**Routes Installation** (`staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/routes/openapi.go`):\n- `InstallV2()` function:\n  - Builds OpenAPI v2 spec from all registered web services\n  - Creates `handler.OpenAPIService` with the spec\n  - Registers the service at `/openapi/v2` endpoint\n  - Prunes default values to keep spec size reasonable\n\n- `InstallV3()` function:\n  - Creates `handler3.OpenAPIService`\n  - Builds OpenAPI v3 specs per group/version from registered web services\n  - Updates the service with specs via `UpdateGroupVersion()`\n  - Registers handlers at `/openapi/v3` endpoint\n\n**OpenAPI v3 Handler** (`vendor/k8s.io/kube-openapi/pkg/handler3/handler.go`):\n- `RegisterOpenAPIV3VersionedService()` method:\n  - Registers `HandleDiscovery()` handler at `/openapi/v3`\n  - Registers `HandleGroupVersion()` handler at `/openapi/v3/` with prefix matching\n\n- `HandleDiscovery()` method:\n  - Serves OpenAPI v3 discovery document\n  - Lists all available group/versions\n\n- `HandleGroupVersion()` method:\n  - Serves the OpenAPI v3 schema for a specific group/version\n  - Extracts group and version from request URL\n  - Returns the corresponding schema\n\nThe OpenAPI v2 handler in `vendor/k8s.io/kube-openapi/pkg/handler/handler.go` follows a similar pattern, registering at `/openapi/v2`.\n\n### 6. Version Conversion\n\nFor clients that need OpenAPI v2 specs, the system can convert v3 to v2 using:\n- `vendor/k8s.io/kube-openapi/pkg/openapiconv/convert.go` - `ConvertV2ToV3()` function\n- Handles path conversion, component schema conversion, and security definition conversion\n\nFor CRDs specifically, `staging/src/k8s.io/apiextensions-apiserver/pkg/controller/openapi/v2/conversion.go` provides:\n- `ToStructuralOpenAPIV2()` function to strip v3-only features from structural schemas\n\n### Flow Summary\n\n```\nCustomResourceDefinition (CRD)\n    ↓ [Validation Schema: JSONSchemaProps]\nNewStructural() in convert.go\n    ↓ [Structural Schema]\ngenerateBuilder() in builder.go\n    ↓ [WebService with routes]\nBuildOpenAPIV3()/BuildOpenAPIV2()\n    ↓ [OpenAPI Spec]\nOpenAPI Controllers (openapi/controller.go, openapiv3/controller.go)\n    ↓ [spec.Swagger or spec3.OpenAPI]\nhandler.OpenAPIService / handler3.OpenAPIService\n    ↓ [HTTP Handler]\nAPI Server Routes: /openapi/v2 and /openapi/v3\n    ↓\nClient Discovery and Schema Validation\n```\n\n### Key Components\n\n1. **CRD Validation Spec**: CustomResourceDefinition with OpenAPIV3Schema field\n2. **Structural Schema**: Internal representation for efficient validation and OpenAPI generation\n3. **Builder**: Converts structural schemas to OpenAPI specs with Kubernetes conventions\n4. **Controllers**: Watch CRDs and keep OpenAPI specs synchronized\n5. **Handlers**: Serve OpenAPI specs via HTTP endpoints\n6. **Endpoints**: `/openapi/v2` (Swagger 2.0) and `/openapi/v3` (OpenAPI 3.0)\n\nThis chain enables clients to discover and validate custom resources at runtime using industry-standard OpenAPI specifications, with automatic updates whenever CRDs change."
